# Docker Compose (Coolify)

Production deploys use [`docker-compose.coolify.yaml`](docker-compose.coolify.yaml) as the **single source of truth**. Local dev uses [`docker-compose.yml`](docker-compose.yml). Operator guide: [docs/deploy-coolify.md](docs/deploy-coolify.md).

**Coolify limitation:** do not use YAML anchors (`x-*`, `&anchor`, `*anchor`). Duplicate `environment` lists per service instead.

**Images:** App tiers use pre-built **`ghcr.io/thravok/elvish-email/<role>:${ELVISH_IMAGE_TAG:-main}`** (not `build:`). Roles: `api`, `mta`, `worker`, `web`, `admin`, `docs`, `scylla-init`. `web`/`admin` write runtime `api-config.js` from env (entrypoint scripts baked in image). `docs` uses profile `docs` (optional).

## Source of truth

Define env vars, storage, ports, and health behavior **in the compose file** ‚Äî not only in the Coolify UI. Coolify reads the file and surfaces `${VAR}` placeholders in the UI.

## Exposing services

| Goal | Pattern |
|------|---------|
| HTTP via Coolify proxy | Assign a domain in Coolify UI; no `ports:` needed. Include container port in domain when not 80 (e.g. `https://app.example.com:8765`). |
| Host port binding | `ports: ["3000:3000"]` ‚Äî bypasses proxy; avoid for private services in shared dev/prod files. Bind to localhost when needed: `127.0.0.1:3000:3000`. |
| Internal only | Omit `ports` and domain; reach via service name: `http://valkey:6379`. |

Do **not** add Traefik labels for Coolify deploys ‚Äî configure domains in the Coolify UI instead.

## Environment variables

```yaml
environment:
  - HARD_CODED=hello                              # passed through; not editable in UI
  - SOME_VAR=${SOME_VAR}                          # editable, uninitialized in UI
  - WITH_DEFAULT=${OTHER:-hello}                  # optional with default
  - REQUIRED=${DATABASE_URL:?}                    # required ‚Äî red border if empty
  - REQUIRED_DEFAULT=${PORT:?8765}                # required with prefilled default
```

- Use `${VAR:?}` for secrets and critical config operators must set.
- Shared Coolify vars: define in compose, then set `VAR={{environment.SHARED_NAME}}` in the UI.
- Magic vars (`SERVICE_URL_*`, `SERVICE_FQDN_*`, `SERVICE_PASSWORD_*`, etc.) are generated from **compose service names** (hyphens ‚Üí underscores in keys, e.g. `mail-mta` ‚Üí `SERVICE_URL_MAIL_MTA_*`). Use **port-suffixed** URLs (`SERVICE_URL_API_8765`, not bare `SERVICE_URL_API`) so custom domains stay in sync. **Declare every `SERVICE_*` name a service references** in that service‚Äôs `environment` list ‚Äî including cross-service refs like `SERVICE_URL_API_8765` on `web`.

```yaml
# ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî port-specific magic vars (prefer SERVICE_URL_*_<port> over generic SERVICE_URL_*)
environment:
  - ELVISH_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=${ELVISH_PUBLIC_BASE_URL:-${SERVICE_URL_WEB_8080:?}}
  - ELVISH_WEB_ORIGINS=${ELVISH_WEB_ORIGINS:-${SERVICE_URL_WEB_8080:?},${SERVICE_URL_ADMIN_8080:?}}
  - VALKEY_PASSWORD=${VALKEY_PASSWORD:-${SERVICE_PASSWORD_64_VALKEY:?}}
  - BLOB_S3_ACCESS_KEY=${BLOB_S3_ACCESS_KEY:-${SERVICE_USER_MINIO:?}}
  - ELVISH_API_BASE=${ELVISH_API_BASE:-${SERVICE_URL_API_8765:?}}

# ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî internal store endpoints (override for predefined-network deploys only)
environment:
  - SCYLLA_HOSTS=${SCYLLA_HOSTS:-scylla:9042}
  - BLOB_S3_ENDPOINT=${BLOB_S3_ENDPOINT:-http://minio:9000}

# ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî hardcoded public URL instead of SERVICE_URL_*
environment:
  - ELVISH_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=https://app.example.com
```

## Coolify-only compose extensions

```yaml
volumes:
  - type: bind
    source: ./srv
    target: /srv
    is_directory: true   # Coolify creates host dir

services:
  migrate:
    exclude_from_hc: true  # one-shot jobs skip stack healthchecks
```

Prefer `configs:` with `content: |` for generated config files when bind-mount content is needed.

## ELVish-specific defaults

- **`api`** (port 8765): JSON API + SSR (`elvishapi`, `ELVISH_SERVE_STATIC=0`); assign a Coolify domain; defaults from `SERVICE_URL_API_8765`.
- **`web`** / **`admin`** (port 8080): nginx static tiers; runtime `api-config.js` from env (scripts baked in image). Assign separate Coolify domains; health probe path **`/healthz`** (not `/` ‚Äî web has no root index).
- **`mail-mta`**: host `ports` for 25/587 ‚Äî HTTP proxy cannot carry SMTP. Internal `:8765` serves `/api/healthz` when `ELVISH_HTTP_ENABLED=1` (compose default); not published to the host.
- **`worker`**, **`cockroach`**, **`valkey`**, **`scylla`**, **`minio`**: internal only ‚Äî no `SERVICE_URL_*` / `SERVICE_FQDN_*` on those services (Coolify would offer a public domain). App tiers connect via `COCKROACH_DSN`, `VALKEY_ADDR`, `SCYLLA_HOSTS`, `BLOB_S3_ENDPOINT` (defaults use Docker service names). **`scylla-init`** (GHCR image) / **`minio-init`** (inline `minio/mc`) gate mail startup. Valkey/MinIO secrets use `SERVICE_PASSWORD_64_VALKEY` and `SERVICE_USER_MINIO` / `SERVICE_PASSWORD_64_MINIO` with `${‚Ä¶:?}` on consumers.
- Compose **`healthcheck`** blocks on app tiers use `-healthcheck` on Go binaries (distroless-safe) or `wget /healthz` on nginx images ‚Äî see [docs/deploy-coolify.md](docs/deploy-coolify.md).
- Keep dev-only `ports:` in `docker-compose.yml`; production exposure goes through Coolify domains or intentional host binds in `docker-compose.coolify.yaml`.

## Predefined networks

Connecting stacks via Coolify's "Connect to Predefined Network" breaks normal Docker DNS ‚Äî use renamed hosts like `postgres-<uuid>` instead of bare service names.
